# Real deploy secrets for wgserver. Copy to deploy.env and fill in.
# This file is gitignored — never commit the populated version.
#
# Minimum to deploy:
DEPLOY_HOST=root@vpn.example.com

# Public IP or FQDN that client .conf files will have in their
# [Peer] Endpoint = ... line. The daemon's wg0 listens on the
# wireguard interface directly, so this is what the CLIENT dials,
# not what the daemon binds to. Default (if unset) is
# "$(hostname):51820" with a loud warning; almost always wrong on a
# real deploy because $(hostname) is a short local name. Set this
# to a public FQDN or IP before running deploy.sh.
# Examples:
#   WGSERVER_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT=203.0.113.10:51820
#   WGSERVER_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT=vpn.example.com:51820
# WGSERVER_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT=

# The operator must write /etc/xray/config.json on the target host
# BEFORE running install.sh (the installer validates it). This file
# is NOT shipped by deploy.sh. The installer does NOT rewrite the
# operator's VLESS Reality secrets — to rotate, edit the file on
# the host and `systemctl restart xray`. See AGENTS.md invariant
# "xray config is operator-managed".
#
# Optional: pin the xray release tag (default: latest from GitHub).
# WGSERVER_XRAY_VERSION=v1.8.20

# Telegram bot (optional — leave empty to disable the bot).
# Get from @BotFather: /newbot, then /token. See deploy README.
WGSERVER_TG_BOT_TOKEN=
WGSERVER_TG_CHAT_ID=0
WGSERVER_TG_QUOTA=2

# Admin UI and /healthz listeners (defaults shown).
WGSERVER_LISTEN_ADDR=127.0.0.1:8080
WGSERVER_HEALTH_ADDR=127.0.0.1:9090

# Optional:
# VERSION=v0.1.0          # override the embedded version string
# REMOTE_TMP=/tmp         # remote staging directory
# ENABLE_UPDATER=1        # 1 to install wgserver-updater + timer, 0 to skip

# MASQUERADE peer traffic in POSTROUTING. By default wgserver
# intentionally does NOT MASQUERADE: peer TCP/UDP goes through
# local xray-core (VLESS Reality) for the exit, so MASQUERADE
# is unnecessary. The trade-off: ICMP (ping, traceroute) and any
# protocol xray doesn't proxy exit the box as 10.0.1.X, which
# the public internet can't route back to (RFC 1918). Set to 1
# to MASQUERADE the peer subnet, restoring classic WG-as-router
# behaviour for non-proxied traffic at the cost of bypassing
# xray for those packets.
# Default: 0
# WGSERVER_MASQUERADE_PEERS=0
